The paper proposes a neural network-based next-song recommender system that utilizes sequential patterns, which is a common approach in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG) for recommendation tasks. The system is also inspired by natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (CL). Additionally, the paper compares the proposed system with several classic recommendation systems, which could fall under the category of software engineering and programming (SD). Finally, the system's performance is evaluated using verification results, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (AI) research.
